**[CRITICAL] `inference/src/lib.rs`:103-125 – Inaccurate approximation for the incomplete beta function.**
The `incomplete_beta` function uses a simple power series expansion. As noted in the code comment, this is not highly accurate. This approximation is only valid for small `x` and can converge very slowly or produce incorrect results for other values. Since this function is fundamental for calculating p-values for both t-tests and F-tests, its inaccuracy compromises the statistical validity of the entire library.

→ **Fix:** Replace the manual implementation with a robust version from a specialized library like `statrs`. This is the standard approach in the Rust ecosystem and will provide a well-tested, accurate implementation.

```rust
