**[HIGH] `stats_models/src/lib.rs`:96-101 – Inefficient and inflexible API design.**
The `Lm::fit` function takes flat `&[f64]` slices and reconstructs matrices internally. This involves unnecessary data copying (lines 115-116) and makes the API awkward for users who already have their data in a matrix structure (e.g., `ndarray::Array2` or `faer::Mat`). Furthermore, the results are copied back into `Vec<f64>` (lines 161-171), and the entire design matrix is cloned into `LmFit` (line 181), leading to high memory usage and performance overhead. This will be a major bottleneck for bootstrapping or large datasets.

